<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2501&amp;p=19305#p19305"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Software interlacing on the NES ?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=2501&amp;p=19305#p19305"><![CDATA[
Not on an NTSC NES. The presence (480i) or absence (240p) of interlacing depends on what happens at the start of vblank (sync signal delayed by 1/2 scanline or not), not what happens at the end of vblank.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Nov 10, 2006 9:09 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
